Saturday night with for some area rivers and streams.
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood

author: Jacob Newton
title: Sioux Falls ice ribbon delayed, won’t open this winter
text:
KELO Sioux Falls Sioux Falls ice ribbon delayed, won’t open this winter Jacob Newton Fri, December 13, 2024 at 5:52 PM UTC 1 min read
SIOUX FALL, S.D. (KELO) — The new ice ribbon at Sioux Falls’ Jacobson Plaza will not be open to skaters this winter.
That’s according to Jackie Nelson, recreation manager for the Sioux Falls Parks and Recreation department, who answered a question about it at the city’s media briefing.
Alcohol a factor in Yankton wrestling meet shooting
“We were hoping for a soft opening for the Jacobson Plaza here after the 1st of the new year,” Nelson said. “Right now due to some construction delays, some weather and some consultant feedback, we’re planning to hold the ribbon for now.”
Advertisement Advertisement Advertisement Nelson said the city is still planning to open the gathering hall and warming house at the site for indoor programming and food and beverage options around mid-February.
“The ice ribbon will not open this winter, at this time,” said Nelson.
The ribbon was expected to be open this winter as recently as November, when city council members expressed concerns about parking for the skaters .
In September, the city claimed the ribbon would be open in the first few weeks of winter in January or February 2025.

title: RxSight launches new Light Adjustable Lens product By Investing.com
text: ALISO VIEJO, Calif. - RxSight, Inc. (NASDAQ: RXST), an ophthalmic medical device company, has announced the commercial release of its latest product, the Light Adjustable Lens+ (LAL+), designed to enhance vision for patients after cataract surgery. The LAL+ joins the company's Light Adjustable Lens platform, which also includes the previously available LAL®. The new LAL+ features a modified aspheric anterior surface aimed at slightly extending the depth of focus by providing a continuous increase in central lens power. This innovation is part of RxSight's adjustable intraocular lens (IOL) technology, which is unique in allowing post-surgery adjustments to optimize patient vision. The launch coincides with the American Society of Cataract and Refractive Surgery (ASCRS) annual meeting, set to take place in Boston from April 5-8, 2024. RxSight's Light Adjustable Lens system, including the LAL and LAL+, will be featured in over 20 scientific papers, posters, and presentations during the event. Notable presentations will include discussions on the benefits of arcuate incisions with a dual-pulsed femtosecond laser, assessing binocular vision post-implantation of the new lens, and refractive and visual outcomes associated with the technology. Moreover, RxSight will host a series of presentations at its booth in the convention exhibit hall, where doctors will share their experiences with the LAL system. These presentations are independent of the official ASCRS program but are expected to provide valuable insights into the practical application and benefits of the adjustable lens technology. The RxSight Light Adjustable Lens system, including the LAL and LAL+, represents the only IOL technology that can be adjusted after cataract surgery, allowing for the customization of vision for patients based on individual needs. This announcement is based on a press release statement from RxSight, Inc. The company's commitment to providing high-quality, customized vision solutions continues to be at the forefront of its product development and customer care initiatives. author: The Independent
title: Snow Whitens Palm Trees on Las Vegas Golf Course
text:
Storyful Snow Whitens Palm Trees on Las Vegas Golf Course Read full article Storyful 12 January 2024 at 0:21 am
Palm trees were whitened as a wintry mix of snow and rain fell in northern and southern parts of the Las Vegas Valley on Thursday morning, January 11.
This video from John McDonough shows snow falling at the Revere Golf Club in Henderson, south of Las Vegas, on Thursday morning.
A day earlier, the temperature in Las Vegas dropped below freezing for the first time this winter, according to the National Weather Service .
The snow didn’t stick around, according to local media , and weather officials said the fast-moving cold front had moved southeast toward Arizona by Thursday afternoon. Credit: John McDonough via Storyful
